<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-06T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="675" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550.E1/241: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-06T20:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 6, 1922—8
                                        p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your 23, May 4, 10 A.M.<note n="20" xml:id="d675fn20">Not printed.</note>
                            The general position set forth in Department’s May 4, 7 P.M. applies
                            also to agreement contemplated in Clause Seven,<note n="21" xml:id="d675fn21">Clause VII of the conditions submitted to the
                                Russian delegation, May 2, <ref target="#pg_783">p.
                                783</ref>.</note> and you may so state in your discretion to
                            representatives <pb facs="0903" n="789" xml:id="pg_789"/> of British and
                            other Governments. Make this known also in your discretion to Soviet
                            representatives. Telegraph exact text of Clause Seven, with any
                            amendments.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>